===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Originally an {{Han compound|禾|口|刀|ls=ic|t1=cereal|tr2=perhaps a bag or rope in this character|t3=knife, blade|nocap=1}}, meaning "to cut the cereal plants, to harvest" (Ji Xusheng 季旭昇); the original shape is linked to the character {{zh-m|𥞥}}.

On bronze inscriptions, the character was stylized into {{zh-m|*柬||bag stuffed with herbs}} + {{zh-m|*刀||knife, blade}} and the original meaning evolved.

